scene.message:
Mark: Kandori!{nl}
You're not getting away!{nl}
Prepare yourself!!{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: ...{wait_fr:60}Found you{nl}
at last...{nl}
You won't escape now!{waitkey}{ret}

Aki: You're so persistent!!{nl}
I won't let you get{nl}
in Papa's way!!{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Stop tormenting people!{nl}
Turn everyone back{nl}
to normal!{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: ...{wait_fr:60}Don't worry.{nl}
I'll do no more than this.{nl}
Anymore...{wait_fr:180} none of it matters.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: What's the deal?!{nl}
Did he just suddenly{nl}
lose all his drive?{waitkey}We psyched ourselves up{nl}
for nothing, c'mon.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Hey!{nl}
Did he chicken out?{nl}
No use apologizing now!{waitkey}{clearbox}Ayase is super ticked off!{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: ...{wait_fr:60}What's your{nl}
game? You think you can{nl}
beg for your life now?{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Man is not strong{nl}
enough to live without{nl}
some goal to strive for...{waitkey}{clearbox}Everyone seeks something,{nl}
however trivial it may be...{nl}
That is why they can{nl}
live so desperately.{waitkey}{clearbox}But...{wait_fr:60} once every wish{nl}
is satisfied, what is{nl}
there left to seek?{waitkey}{clearbox}At the summit you reach{nl}
by granting wish on wish...{nl}
lies only endless{nl}
emptiness and solitude.{waitkey}{clearbox}So is it not better never{nl}
to climb the stairs you set{nl}
yourself? That way...{waitkey}you can dream forever.{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: I... kept climbing{nl}
the stairs to destroy{nl}
this worthless world...{waitkey}{clearbox}But none of it matters now.{nl}
For me as I am now...{nl}
nothing is impossible.{waitkey}{clearbox}Heh...{wait_fr:60} Winds of solitude{nl}
and emptiness rage about me.{nl}
So this is the realm{nl}
of a god?{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Young one,{wait_fr:88}{nl}
I let you come this far{nl}
to ask you that.{waitkey}For what do you all live?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: That's right!{nl}
What we live for...{waitkey}{clearbox}Maybe I'll never{nl}
know the answer...{wait_fr:88}{nl}
But! I believe in myself!{waitkey}{clearbox}I'll live a life{nl}
with no regrets!{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: No, no!{nl}
What we live for...{waitkey}{clearbox}Maybe I'll never{nl}
know the answer...{wait_fr:88}{nl}
But! I believe in myself!{waitkey}{clearbox}I'll live a life{nl}
with no regrets!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: You dummy.{nl}
A grown man like you{nl}
doesn't even get that?{waitkey}{clearbox}It's so you can shine{nl}
bright in each and every{nl}
moment, obviously!{waitkey}{clearbox}Your vibe's too gloomy.{nl}
So bad!{nl}
Get a more positive attitude!{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: ...{wait_fr:60}It's obvious.{nl}
It's to kill you!{waitkey}{clearbox}That settles things with{nl}
this filthy blood. If I don't,{nl}
I can't make my mother happy!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: To protect those{nl}
dear to me! The ones here are{nl}
my true friends, the kind{nl}
I can open my heart to...{waitkey}{clearbox}I can't lose the precious{nl}
things I've finally found!{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: To surpass myself!{nl}
I'm done with lying and{nl}
tucking my tail!{waitkey}{clearbox}I've decided!{nl}
I'll take down the geezer{nl}
and say goodbye to my{nl}
phony self too!{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: For my future husband!{nl}
Ayase's the one who'll{nl}
struggle later in life.{waitkey}{clearbox}A small house is fine, but{nl}
a cute one. And the kids,{nl}
maybe a boy and a girl.{waitkey}{clearbox}I'll name them Takuya and{nl}
Yuki, and then...{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Kandori...{wait_fr:60} Stop this.{nl}
Such excessive bravado{nl}
is painful to watch.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: You must realize it.{nl}
That the place you reached{nl}
by using people is no{nl}
throne of god.{waitkey}That you've done nothing{nl}
by yourself...{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: You're suffering.{nl}
You despair at yourself,{nl}
at being able to live{nl}
no other way than this.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Your wish to erase{nl}
mankind, like hers,{nl}
{wait_fr:88}springs from dread{nl}
of your own future.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: To want to change,{wait_fr:60}{nl}
unable to change,{wait_fr:60}{nl}
wishing to disappear...{waitkey}{clearbox}Did you think one man's{nl}
fear would grow lighter{nl}
if all mankind bore it?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Why not stop using{nl}
grand pretexts to justify{nl}
your inferiority complex?{waitkey}{clearbox}You, more than anyone,{nl}
must see how absurd{nl}
you are.{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: ...{wait_fr:60}So much abuse{nl}
hurled at a god. I cannot{nl}
let it pass.{waitkey}I'll send you to your{nl}
end with my own hands.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Tch.{nl}
So you finally feel{nl}
like it!{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Can you defeat me?{nl}
Can you protect these{nl}
precious things of yours?{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: ...{wait_fr:60}I'll protect{nl}
my mother and these guys.{nl}
By killing you.{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Young one...{nl}
I have not heard{nl}
your answer.{waitkey}{ret}
